transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, yes, I got my delivery today of the generic Viagra, but I was supposed to get the AGV, not the regular Viagra.

Speaker 1: And what's your first and last name, sir?

Speaker 2: Michael Nilsen.

Speaker 1: And you got the wrong thing, Mr. Nilsen?

Speaker 2: Well, I think so. You guys delivered the wrong one.

Speaker 1: You don't see the AGV indication on the label there anywhere?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Do you have the pills there in front of you?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: What do the markings on the actual physical pills say, please?

Speaker 2: Take one out of the bottle, Mr. Nilsen.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: They say AC340.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you're absolutely right. Those are wrong, Michael.

Speaker 2: I'm really sorry about that. You got the wrong thing.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm really sorry about that.

Speaker 2: What I'm going to do for you, of course, I'm going to send you out a replacement order stat.

Speaker 1: I'm already working on that with our pharmacy for you.

Speaker 2: Fifteen pills are going to come out at no cost.

Speaker 1: Of course, you've already paid.

Speaker 2: The pills that you have there, they're just made at our American facility.

Speaker 1: They're still, you know, generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: If they don't work for you, you're more than welcome to toss them.

Speaker 1: If you want to save them for like a rainy day, you can.

Speaker 2: You don't have to send them back or anything.

Speaker 1: I'm going to send you this replacement order of 15 pills.

Speaker 2: You'll see them come early next week, okay?

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem. Thank you, sir.

Speaker 1: And you're at 860 East Grangeville Boulevard, Unit 150, right, Hanford?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right. Perfect. Yep. So you'll see those come out early next week, okay?

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye now.

Speaker 2: Bye.
